  "texts": [
    "Of course, the correlation with human norms was far from perfect, particularly for dimensions such as semantic dominance (though it is unclear what human inter-annotator agreement was for these dimensions).",
    "This raises an important question about the degree-offit required to augment datasets with LLM-generated norms: how successful must an LLM be-relative to a human baseline-to be used either in norming stimuli or increasing the size of a dataset?",
    "This question depends on a researcher's goals and on the degree of precision required.",
    "Notably, LLM-generated norms performed much better for some dimensions than others.",
    "If this gradient in performance is systematic, then perhaps researchers could rely more on LLMs for those specific dimensions (e.g., contextualized concreteness), and focus their energies on collecting human data for other dimensions (e.g., semantic dominance); again, in each case, comparison to a human baseline would be essential."
  ],
